subtests.name: A sync access handle opens in readwrite mode by default
An access handle in readwrite mode has a mode property equal to readwrite
When there's an open access handle in readwrite mode on a file, cannot open another access handle of another mode on that same file
When there's an open access handle in readwrite mode on a file, can open another access handle of any mode on a different file
After an access handle in readwrite mode on a file has been closed, can open another access handle of any mode on the same file
An access handle in read-only mode has a mode property equal to read-only
When there's an open access handle in read-only mode on a file, cannot open another access handle of another mode on that same file
When there's an open access handle in read-only mode on a file, can open another access handle of any mode on a different file
After an access handle in read-only mode on a file has been closed, can open another access handle of any mode on the same file
An access handle in readwrite-unsafe mode has a mode property equal to readwrite-unsafe
When there's an open access handle in readwrite-unsafe mode on a file, cannot open another access handle of another mode on that same file
When there's an open access handle in readwrite-unsafe mode on a file, can open another access handle of any mode on a different file
After an access handle in readwrite-unsafe mode on a file has been closed, can open another access handle of any mode on the same file
